 10-10-2020 19:04:00  According to KwaZulu-Natal Emergency Medical Services spokesperson Robert McKenzie, paramedics were at the scene of the crash. He said the vehicle veered off the road, down an embankment and came to rest near a river. "Tragically, 12 people have sustained fatal injuries in this crash, including a child. Paramedics from several private ambulance services as well as KZN Emergency Medical Services are currently at the scene."  